1
00:02:44,950 --> 00:02:46,540
你说对了 乔治
You were right, George.

2
00:02:46,680 --> 00:02:48,960
我们中有叛徒
We have a traitor in the house.

3
00:02:50,300 --> 00:02:53,200
这上面有五个名字
There are five names on there.

4
00:02:53,340 --> 00:02:55,890
你妻子也是其中之一
Your wife’s one of them.

5
00:02:56,030 --> 00:02:57,240
为什么
Why is that?

6
00:02:57,380 --> 00:02:58,730
你让我查所有人
You asked me to look at everyone.

7
00:02:58,860 --> 00:03:00,520
我查了
I looked.

8
00:03:00,660 --> 00:03:02,350
她有权限 有动机
She has the security clearance, she has the motive,

9
00:03:02,490 --> 00:03:04,420
也有能力
and she has the capability.

10
00:03:04,560 --> 00:03:06,730
我必须得把她列进去
I had to put her down.

11
00:03:07,560 --> 00:03:09,010
你大概要多久
How long do you think you’ll need?

12
00:03:09,150 --> 00:03:10,810
给我两周时间
Give me two weeks.

13
00:03:10,940 --> 00:03:13,050
如果他们真的按计划用了死危病毒
If Severus is deployed as intended,

14
00:03:13,190 --> 00:03:15,120
上千无辜的人都会死
thousands of innocent people will die.

15
00:03:15,260 --> 00:03:17,230
好吧 一周
Okay. One week.

16
00:03:18,160 --> 00:03:21,230
如果真是凯瑟琳 你真的下得了手吗
If it is Kathryn, do you really think you can do that?

17
00:03:23,890 --> 00:03:25,030
安娜怎么样了
How’s Anna?

18
00:03:27,720 --> 00:03:29,890
还气着呢
Still mad.

19
00:03:30,030 --> 00:03:32,480
-很抱歉 -我犯了一个错误 就这样
-I’m sorry. -I made a mistake, that’s all.

20
00:03:32,620 --> 00:03:34,070
她没法放下
She just can’t let it go.

21
00:03:34,210 --> 00:03:35,660
她会的 最终会的
She will, eventually.

22
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:37,380
真的
Yeah?

23
00:03:37,520 --> 00:03:41,390
有些事情最好的处理方式就是避而不谈
Some things really are best swept under the rug.

24
00:03:43,290 --> 00:03:45,570
我就是觉得要是没那么简单就好了
I just wish it wasn’t so fucking easy.

25
00:03:46,740 --> 00:03:48,330
出轨
To cheat.

26
00:03:48,460 --> 00:03:49,400
对我们来说
For us.

27
00:03:49,530 --> 00:03:51,400
嗯哼
Mm.

28
00:03:54,060 --> 00:03:57,020
不是所有人都向往你那样明目张胆的一夫一妻制 乔治
Not everyone aspires to your flagrant monogamy, George.

29
00:03:58,090 --> 00:04:01,100
如果你想让安娜消消气
If you’d like Anna to be less angry,

30
00:04:01,240 --> 00:04:03,890
可以考虑回趟家
you might consider going home.

31
00:04:12,800 --> 00:04:15,040
祝你顺利找到内奸
Good luck finding the rat.

32
00:05:35,050 --> 00:05:37,680
我能感觉到你在盯着我看
I can feel when you’re watching me.

33
00:05:38,780 --> 00:05:40,090
抱歉
Sorry.

34
00:05:40,890 --> 00:05:42,850
我很喜欢
I like it.

35
00:05:45,440 --> 00:05:46,930
我知道这不是你喜欢的那种
I understand this is not

36
00:05:47,070 --> 00:05:48,650
简单的晚餐
the casual dinner you’d prefer.

37
00:05:48,790 --> 00:05:51,690
是啊 这次是群不同寻常的人
Yeah. It’s an unusual group.

38
00:05:52,620 --> 00:05:57,320
数据收集员 两名特工 还有个内部的心理医生
Data scraper, two agents and the in-house shrink.

39
00:05:58,660 --> 00:06:01,360
我们这次要找什么
What are we hunting this time?

40
00:06:01,490 --> 00:06:03,120
死危病毒
Severus.

41
00:06:04,530 --> 00:06:06,880
你觉得他们中有人拿了
And you think one of them took it?

42
00:06:07,020 --> 00:06:08,640
有可能
Possibly.

43
00:06:08,780 --> 00:06:10,020
嗯
Hmm.

44
00:06:10,950 --> 00:06:15,270
咱们有段时间没请叛徒共进晚餐了
It’s been a while since we had a traitor to dinner.

45
00:06:15,400 --> 00:06:17,370
至少是在已知有叛徒的情况下
At least knowingly.

46
00:06:18,930 --> 00:06:20,890
我们不该讨论这个
We shouldn’t be discussing this.

47
00:06:21,030 --> 00:06:22,790
是啊 大概不该讨论
No, probably not.

48
00:06:23,760 --> 00:06:26,480
我以为你要从测谎仪开始
I would’ve thought you’d start with polygraphs.

49
00:06:26,620 --> 00:06:29,870
我想试试一开始优雅一些
I wanted to try something more elegant first.

50
00:06:32,110 --> 00:06:33,900
菜单上有什么
What’s on the menu?

51
00:06:34,040 --> 00:06:35,910
乐趣和游戏
Fun and games.

52
00:06:36,910 --> 00:06:38,910
事后需要清理现场吗
Will there be a mess to clean up?

53
00:06:39,050 --> 00:06:40,290
如果进展顺利的话
With any luck.

54
00:06:43,430 --> 00:06:45,810
-它们很适合你 -嗯
-They suit you. -Mm.

55
00:06:45,950 --> 00:06:48,580
不你花太多钱了
No, you spent too much.

56
00:06:48,710 --> 00:06:51,510
你总这么在意钱也太无趣了
It’s boring how much you think about money.

57
00:06:53,790 --> 00:06:56,720
你总这么不在乎钱也太吓人了
It’s terrifying how much you don’t.

58
00:06:58,480 --> 00:07:00,590
别吃鹰嘴豆咖喱
Avoid the chana masala.

59
00:07:00,730 --> 00:07:04,320
里面有一定量的DZM 5
Contains a healthy amount of DZM 5.

60
00:07:04,450 --> 00:07:08,220
亲爱的 你可不能给我们的客人下药啊
Darling, you may not dose our guests.

61
00:07:09,460 --> 00:07:11,740
他们中有人在说谎
One of them is a liar.

62
00:07:11,870 --> 00:07:13,390
我想知道是谁
I want to know which.

63
00:07:13,530 --> 00:07:15,260
我从没想过这会发生
♪ I never thought it would happen ♪

64
00:07:15,400 --> 00:07:18,020
在我和克拉珀姆的那个女孩身上
♪ With me and the girl from Clapham ♪

65
00:07:18,160 --> 00:07:19,950
在那刮风的公地上
♪ Out on the windy common ♪

66
00:07:20,090 --> 00:07:21,850
那一夜我至今难忘
♪ That night I ain’t forgotten ♪

67
00:07:21,990 --> 00:07:23,610
她分配着生活所需
♪ When she dealt out the rations ♪

68
00:07:23,750 --> 00:07:25,300
带着一些激情
♪ With some or other passions... ♪

69
00:07:25,440 --> 00:07:27,100
-马修 -您好 先生
-Matthew. -Hello, sir.

70
00:07:27,230 --> 00:07:29,580
我想给靠门的那桌买单
I want to settle up for the table by the door.

71
00:07:29,720 --> 00:07:31,520
-当然 -然后我要双份的尊美醇威士忌
-Of course. -And I’ll have a double Jameson.

72
00:07:31,650 --> 00:07:32,760
马上先生
Straightaway, sir.

73
00:07:35,480 --> 00:07:37,970
我知道他们其实也没有那么老
I know they’re not that much older, really,

74
00:07:38,110 --> 00:07:41,420
但我还是觉得像是要去我爸妈家一样
but I kind of feel like I’m going to my parents’ house.

75
00:07:41,560 --> 00:07:44,840
如果我爸妈没离婚也不恨彼此的话
If-if they weren’t divorced and didn’t hate each other.

76
00:07:44,980 --> 00:07:46,390
反正 我知道的是
Well, here’s what I know.

77
00:07:46,530 --> 00:07:47,910
不会有人两次邀请你共进晚餐
You don’t get invited to dinner twice

78
00:07:48,050 --> 00:07:49,950
如果你第一次拒绝了他们的话
if you say no the first time.

79
00:07:50,090 --> 00:07:52,020
但为什么是现在
But why now?

80
00:07:52,160 --> 00:07:54,120
还只提前24小时通知
With 24 hours’ notice?

81
00:07:54,260 --> 00:07:55,400
以及为什么是我们?
And why us?

82
00:07:55,540 --> 00:07:57,510
我们都在一起工作啊
We all work together.

83
00:07:57,640 --> 00:07:59,750
请两对在同一领域工作的夫妻 也没那么牵强
Two couples in the same field. It’s not that much of a reach.

84
00:07:59,890 --> 00:08:01,720
所以你觉得是他们自发想邀请我们
So you believe this was just spontaneous?

85
00:08:01,860 --> 00:08:04,890
至少在我看到其他征兆之前会这么认为
I’m assuming so until I see reason to believe otherwise.

86
00:08:05,030 --> 00:08:06,930
你和弗雷迪要面对面坐
You and Freddie sitting across from each other

87
00:08:07,070 --> 00:08:08,720
即使在那件事之后
after what just happened?

88
00:08:08,860 --> 00:08:10,550
他可能是在挑衅你
That could be read as provocative.

89
00:08:10,690 --> 00:08:13,110
弗雷迪挺好的
Freddie’s fine.

90
00:08:13,250 --> 00:08:14,280
对吧
Right?

91
00:08:15,700 --> 00:08:17,460
我怎么会知道
How should I know?

92
00:08:17,600 --> 00:08:18,840
问心理医生去
Ask the shrink.

93
00:08:18,980 --> 00:08:20,560
你们觉得是谁想出来请我们的呢
Whose idea was it, do you think?

94
00:08:20,700 --> 00:08:22,260
-乔治还是凯瑟琳 -乔治
-George or Kathryn? -STOKES and CLARISSA: George.

95
00:08:22,390 --> 00:08:24,460
-抱歉抱歉 非常抱歉 -天呐 弗雷迪
-Sorry, sorry. So sorry. -For fuck’s sake, Freddie.

96
00:08:24,600 --> 00:08:26,190
明明是你订的桌子
I mean, you booked the table.

97
00:08:26,330 --> 00:08:27,540
是你想在赴宴前碰头的
You’re the one that wanted to meet beforehand.

98
00:08:27,670 --> 00:08:29,060
完全是我的错 我承认
I am absolutely at fault, I admit it.

99
00:08:29,190 --> 00:08:31,200
沃恩医生 如果她可以这么说的话
And Dr. Vaughan, were she allowed to say so,

100
00:08:31,330 --> 00:08:33,130
会说我的长期迟到行为中
would claim there’s a certain hostility

101
00:08:33,270 --> 00:08:34,510
带有某种敌意
in my chronic tardiness.

102
00:08:34,650 --> 00:08:36,200
但为了弥补你们
But in order to make it up to you all,

103
00:08:36,340 --> 00:08:37,340
我已经给大家结完了帐 并给了很多小费
I have paid the bill and tipped like a gangster.

104
00:08:37,480 --> 00:08:38,930
哦 拜托
Oh, come on.

105
00:08:39,070 --> 00:08:41,000
我们相聚在此是要庆祝詹姆斯实至名归的
We are celebrating James’s well-deserved,

106
00:08:41,140 --> 00:08:43,760
飞速晋升
meteoric ascent through the ranks.

107
00:08:43,900 --> 00:08:45,280
干杯
Cheers.

108
00:08:50,420 --> 00:08:52,220
-走吗 -好
-Shall we? -Right.

109
00:08:53,840 --> 00:08:55,360
等等
Wait.

110
00:08:56,980 --> 00:08:59,910
我以为你会给我点建议呢 之后该怎么表现
I was hoping for some pointers. I mean, how shall I behave?

111
00:09:00,050 --> 00:09:03,710
称赞他的厨艺 然后一切都会好的
Praise his cooking, and I promise all will be magical.

112
00:09:16,930 --> 00:09:18,070
-嗨 -凯瑟琳
- Hello. - Kathryn.

113
00:09:18,210 --> 00:09:19,110
-嗨 -非常准时
-Hello. -On time and everything.

114
00:09:19,240 --> 00:09:21,660
-进来吧 -谢谢
-Come in. -Thank you.

115
00:09:21,800 --> 00:09:22,830
这个给我吧
Oh, shall I take that?

116
00:09:22,970 --> 00:09:24,800
不用 我拿到厨房
No, I’ll take it to the kitchen.

117
00:09:24,940 --> 00:09:26,560
快进来吧 是啊 外面很冷吧
Come in. Yes, it’s cold, isn’t it?

118
00:09:26,700 --> 00:09:27,910
嗨
Hello.

119
00:09:28,050 --> 00:09:29,390
-很高兴见到你 -好了
-Lovely to see you. -All right.

120
00:09:29,530 --> 00:09:30,570
-把外套给我吧 -哇
-I should take your coat. -Wow.

121
00:09:30,700 --> 00:09:32,390
谢谢
Thank you.

122
00:09:32,530 --> 00:09:35,710
你们的房子 真漂亮
This is, um... beautiful.

123
00:09:35,850 --> 00:09:37,850
哦 是吗
Oh, yeah.

124
00:09:37,990 --> 00:09:39,920
这就是没孩子的快乐 对吧
The joys of not having children, hey?

125
00:09:41,470 --> 00:09:42,820
-你想喝点什么 -朗姆
-What would you like to drink? -Rum.

126
00:09:42,960 --> 00:09:44,610
-朗姆 -嗯哼
-Rum. -Mmm.

127
00:09:45,820 --> 00:09:47,690
-98年的红酒 -对
-’98 for the table. -Right.

128
00:09:47,820 --> 00:09:49,100
真是太棒了
Oh, yes, lovely.

129
00:09:51,240 --> 00:09:53,520
我们赶紧把这事聊开吧
Should we get this over with?

130
00:09:53,660 --> 00:09:56,070
我懂你为什么选他
I get it, why you went with him.

131
00:09:56,210 --> 00:09:58,940
-是吗 -詹姆斯是明智之选
-Yes? -James is the smart play.

132
00:09:59,080 --> 00:10:01,290
年轻 积极进取 而且
Young, aggressive and...

133
00:10:01,420 --> 00:10:03,360
该怎么说呢
How shall we say it?

134
00:10:03,490 --> 00:10:05,080
还没叛变
Uncompromised.

135
00:10:05,220 --> 00:10:06,770
我一直希望是你
I’d always hoped it would be you.

136
00:10:06,910 --> 00:10:08,290
我喝太多酒 操太多人
I drink too much, I fuck too much,

137
00:10:08,430 --> 00:10:10,120
还欠了一屁股债
and I owe more than I’m worth.

138
00:10:13,570 --> 00:10:16,890
药也成了一个问题
The pills are becoming a problem as well.

139
00:10:17,030 --> 00:10:20,240
我很庆幸能向你吐露我的真心 乔治
I’m so glad I can confide in you, George.

140
00:10:21,650 --> 00:10:23,480
我得去换衣服了
I need to change.

141
00:10:27,830 --> 00:10:29,520
放过他们吧
Oh, give them a break.

142
00:10:29,660 --> 00:10:32,900
国家网络安全中心里大多数都是25岁左右的小孩
Most of NCSC is 25-year-olds.

143
00:10:33,040 --> 00:10:34,590
他们都在瞎胡闹呢
They were just mucking around,

144
00:10:34,730 --> 00:10:36,350
试图对一台核心路由器进行零日攻击
trying to zero-day a central router.

145
00:10:36,490 --> 00:10:39,320
他们也没想到能把整个系统搞崩溃
They didn’t know they’d brick the whole system.

146
00:10:39,460 --> 00:10:42,640
等会儿 叙利亚 2012?
Wait. Syria 2012?

147
00:10:42,780 --> 00:10:44,500
那是你们干的
That was you?

148
00:10:44,640 --> 00:10:46,020
-是我们干的 -我不知道
-That was us? -I don’t know.

149
00:10:46,160 --> 00:10:47,610
我不在那边工作
I don’t work on that side of the house.

150
00:10:47,750 --> 00:10:49,640
那次任务做得干净利落 我看过相关文件
That op was tight. I’ve read that string.

151
00:10:49,780 --> 00:10:51,400
代码也很漂亮
It’s a very sexy piece of code.

152
00:10:51,540 --> 00:10:54,060
一切都安然无恙 直到斯诺登冒出头来
Mm. It was all fine till little Eddie Snowden

153
00:10:54,200 --> 00:10:57,240
把所有人暴露了个精光 真是个烂摊子
decided to call everybody out, said it was a fuckup.

154
00:10:57,380 --> 00:10:59,690
那之后阿萨德就被关停了 不是吗
It shut Assad’s ass right down, didn’t it?

155
00:10:59,830 --> 00:11:02,480
死了多少平民
How many civilians died as a result?

156
00:11:02,620 --> 00:11:04,070
为了更伟大的利益
Greater good.

157
00:11:04,210 --> 00:11:06,250
没道德的人都不怎么样
Yeah, I don’t find amorality attractive.

158
00:11:06,380 --> 00:11:08,870
那你只好要么放弃工作 要么放弃性生活了
Then give up either your profession or your sex life.

159
00:11:09,010 --> 00:11:11,600
我猜 两周吧
I give it two weeks.

160
00:11:11,740 --> 00:11:13,010
太乐观了
Optimistic.

161
00:11:13,150 --> 00:11:15,430
上峰为难你了吗
Did you get hell from oversight?

162
00:11:15,570 --> 00:11:17,020
-没什么 -拜托
-Nothing I couldn’t handle. -Oh, please.

163
00:11:17,150 --> 00:11:18,430
委员会只让凯瑟琳不好过了一次
The committee fucked with Kathryn exactly once.

164
00:11:18,570 --> 00:11:20,020
一半的委员就丢掉了任务
Half of them lost their assignments.

165
00:11:20,160 --> 00:11:21,400
睚眦必报嘛
’Cause that’s what bad bitches do.

166
00:11:25,540 --> 00:11:27,200
对了 鹰嘴豆咖喱真好吃
Chana masala is fantastic, by the way.

167
00:11:27,340 --> 00:11:28,440
非常美味
Absolutely delicious.

168
00:11:28,580 --> 00:11:29,890
-嗯 -谢谢
- Mm. - Thank you.

169
00:11:30,030 --> 00:11:31,690
拜托
Come on.

170
00:11:31,820 --> 00:11:33,340
我们在叙利亚干的事可不算是最糟糕的
Syria’s hardly the worst thing we’ve ever done.

171
00:11:33,480 --> 00:11:35,140
我曾经曝光过我孩子的老师是个恋童癖
I once outed my kid’s teacher as a pedophile

172
00:11:35,280 --> 00:11:36,280
就为了把他炒掉
just to get him fired.

173
00:11:36,410 --> 00:11:37,590
哦
Oh.

174
00:11:37,730 --> 00:11:39,350
猜到了
Figures.

175
00:11:39,490 --> 00:11:41,070
结果发现那个人的八岁小孩长了皮疹
Turns out the guy’s eight-year-old had a rash.

176
00:11:41,210 --> 00:11:42,660
他真不应该发那些照片
Guess he shouldn’t have emailed those pictures.

177
00:11:42,800 --> 00:11:44,320
真是让人讨厌 弗雷迪
That is uniquely loathsome, Freddie.

178
00:11:44,460 --> 00:11:45,700
看图说话嘛 怎么对我有利怎么来
You hand me an angle, I play it.

179
00:11:45,840 --> 00:11:47,700
新来的老师现在给Matty打分是A
New teacher gave Matty an "A."

180
00:11:47,840 --> 00:11:49,630
-少惹在特工爸爸们 -我们都是烂人
-Don’t fuck with SIS dad. -So we’re all horrible people.

181
00:11:49,770 --> 00:11:51,400
这是你想说的重点
Is that what the point is here?

182
00:11:51,530 --> 00:11:52,880
我想说的是 「复杂」 的人
