01:20:20,780 --> 01:20:22,050
工作还是社交
Work or social?

1309
01:20:22,190 --> 01:20:23,740
是
Yes.

1310
01:20:26,020 --> 01:20:27,680
我以为只有我一个
I thought it was just me.

1311
01:20:27,820 --> 01:20:28,990
我们都以为
We all did.

1312
01:20:32,750 --> 01:20:34,200
所以晚饭在哪里
So where’s this fucking dinner?

1313
01:20:34,340 --> 01:20:36,340
-我没做饭 -我们有个游戏要玩
-I didn’t cook. -We have a game.

1314
01:20:36,480 --> 01:20:38,070
哦 操 认真的吗
Ah, shit. Really?

1315
01:20:38,210 --> 01:20:40,240
我不愿意配合你的游戏
I don’t think I’m willing to submit to this.

1316
01:20:40,380 --> 01:20:41,690
这是游戏规则
And here’s how it works.

1317
01:20:41,830 --> 01:20:43,390
围着桌子一圈
We go around the table

1318
01:20:43,520 --> 01:20:46,320
乔治会问你们每人一个问题
and George will ask each one of you a question.

1319
01:20:46,460 --> 01:20:48,800
如果答错了 就输了
And if you get it wrong, you lose.

1320
01:20:48,940 --> 01:20:49,910
这不合理
This is inappropriate.

1321
01:20:50,050 --> 01:20:52,220
输家
And the loser

1322
01:20:52,360 --> 01:20:54,150
别想活着走出去
doesn’t get up from the table.

1323
01:20:57,160 --> 01:20:58,990
-我操 -你疯了吗
-For fuck’s sake. -Are you out of your mind?

1324
01:20:59,130 --> 01:21:00,400
你们俩疯了 我发誓
The two of you, I swear to God.

1325
01:21:00,540 --> 01:21:02,540
-我要走了 -坐下
-I’m leaving. -Sit down.

1326
01:21:02,680 --> 01:21:03,850
乔治和凯瑟琳诚挚地邀请你们
You are cordially invited to an evening

1327
01:21:03,990 --> 01:21:06,620
度过一个有趣的夜晚
of fun and games with George and Kathryn.

1328
01:21:06,750 --> 01:21:08,480
这是一条新地毯
That’s a new rug.

1329
01:21:08,620 --> 01:21:10,310
如果你们想在OSRAC委员会面前回答问题的话
Anyone who’d prefer to answer the questions

1330
01:21:10,450 --> 01:21:13,620
就走吧
in front of an OSRAC committee is free to go.

1331
01:21:13,760 --> 01:21:15,450
为什么这里有一个新地毯
Why is there a new rug?

1332
01:21:15,590 --> 01:21:17,380
你们精神错乱了 所有人都是 你们意识到了吗
You’re disturbed. All of you. Do you realize that?

1333
01:21:17,520 --> 01:21:18,970
你疯了
You’re sick!

1334
01:21:19,110 --> 01:21:20,590
你们才做过爱吧
I mean, you just fuck each other, literally,

1335
01:21:20,730 --> 01:21:21,980
来来回回 反反复复
and back and forth and back and forth.

1336
01:21:22,110 --> 01:21:23,320
那栋该死的楼里
Is there one normal person

1337
01:21:23,460 --> 01:21:25,190
就没有一个正常人吗
inside that entire fucking building?

1338
01:21:25,320 --> 01:21:26,390
行
Fine!

1339
01:21:26,530 --> 01:21:28,600
我没什么好隐瞒的
I’ve got nothing to hide.

1340
01:21:28,740 --> 01:21:30,600
那就从你开始
Then we’ll start with you.

1341
01:21:30,740 --> 01:21:32,880
你第一次和弗雷迪上床是什么时候
When did you first sleep with Freddie?

1342
01:21:34,820 --> 01:21:36,130
哦 真恶心
Oh, that’s just gross.

1343
01:21:36,270 --> 01:21:37,400
下作
Sick.

1344
01:21:37,540 --> 01:21:38,850
我道歉
My apologies.

1345
01:21:38,990 --> 01:21:41,200
虽然有失风度但很有必要
That was ungentlemanly but necessary.

1346
01:21:41,340 --> 01:21:43,270
沃恩博士就是弗雷迪在克拉肯威尔
Dr. Vaughan is the woman Freddie’s been meeting

1347
01:21:43,410 --> 01:21:45,210
捷特酒店私会的那个女人
at the Zetter Hotel in Clerkenwell.

1348
01:21:45,340 --> 01:21:46,930
狗娘养的
You motherfucker.

1349
01:21:47,070 --> 01:21:48,830
七八周前
Seven or eight weeks ago.

1350
01:21:48,970 --> 01:21:50,900
-谢谢 -这是在开玩笑么
- Thank you. - Is that a joke?

1351
01:21:51,040 --> 01:21:53,280
和他 为什么
With him? Why?

1352
01:21:53,420 --> 01:21:55,280
这是操纵手段
Manipulation.

1353
01:21:55,420 --> 01:21:57,320
她认为迟早需要从他身上获取情报
She thought she’d need something from him eventually.

1354
01:21:57,460 --> 01:21:59,390
得了吧 别这么混蛋 有没有可能只是
Ah, come on. Don’t be a prick. Isn’t it just possible...

1355
01:21:59,530 --> 01:22:01,980
不可能
No, it isn’t.

1356
01:22:02,120 --> 01:22:03,570
他说得对
He’s right.

1357
01:22:03,710 --> 01:22:06,120
在重新定位被发现后
After the redirect was discovered,

1358
01:22:06,260 --> 01:22:08,370
你通知了沃恩博士对吗
you alerted Dr. Vaughan, didn’t you?

1359
01:22:08,500 --> 01:22:11,820
没错
Yes, that’s right.

1360
01:22:12,820 --> 01:22:14,610
你会想知道这个的
You’ll want to know about this.

1361
01:22:14,750 --> 01:22:16,000
我要你办件事
I need you to do something.

1362
01:22:16,130 --> 01:22:17,720
我任你摆布 什么事
I am putty in your hands. What is it?

1363
01:22:17,860 --> 01:22:20,650
你告诉我重新定位的时候
So, you told me about the redirect,

1364
01:22:20,790 --> 01:22:24,000
知道我会采取行动为乔治打掩护
knowing that I would take action to cover for George.

1365
01:22:24,140 --> 01:22:26,210
他接下来三小时会穿过波兰
He’s traveling across Poland for the next three hours.

1366
01:22:26,350 --> 01:22:27,320
别等了
Don’t wait.

1367
01:22:38,050 --> 01:22:39,740
是
Yes.

1368
01:22:39,880 --> 01:22:41,740
克拉丽莎
Clarissa.

1369
01:22:43,090 --> 01:22:44,750
你他妈想干嘛
What the fuck do you want?

1370
01:22:45,750 --> 01:22:47,790
来祝贺你
Only to congratulate you.

1371
01:22:47,920 --> 01:22:51,100
你是我见过最会操纵测谎仪的人
You’re the best manipulator of the polygraph I’ve ever seen.

1372
01:22:52,820 --> 01:22:54,520
-我没撒谎 -我知道
-I didn’t lie. -I know.

1373
01:22:54,650 --> 01:22:55,970
你不需要撒谎
You didn’t need to.

1374
01:22:56,100 --> 01:22:58,140
你和这些事毫无瓜葛
You had nothing to do with any of it.

1375
01:22:59,690 --> 01:23:02,870
在电影院留票让我发现是你的主意
Was it your idea to plant the movie ticket so I’d find it

1376
01:23:03,010 --> 01:23:04,940
还是别人的
or someone else’s?

1377
01:23:05,080 --> 01:23:06,910
什么电影票
What movie ticket?

1378
01:23:07,050 --> 01:23:08,390
确实引起了我的注意
Did catch my eye.

1379
01:23:08,530 --> 01:23:10,530
以我的专业性判断这并不难
Not so hard to do, given my profession.

1380
01:23:10,670 --> 01:23:12,260
你他妈在说什么鬼话 乔治
The hell are you talking about, George?

1381
01:23:12,400 --> 01:23:14,880
是施蒂格利茨先找你提议
Was Stieglitz the one who came to you with the idea

1382
01:23:15,020 --> 01:23:16,810
偷走死危病毒的吗
of stealing Severus?

1383
01:23:16,950 --> 01:23:20,160
这样最合理
That would make the most sense.

1384
01:23:20,300 --> 01:23:22,890
既能扰乱莫斯科 又能陷害威胁施蒂格利茨的凯瑟琳
To destabilize Moscow, to implicate Kathryn,

1385
01:23:23,030 --> 01:23:26,200
还能把我从你路上踢开
who threatened Stieglitz, and to move me out of your way.

1386
01:23:26,340 --> 01:23:28,450
一举三得
Three birds, one stone.

1387
01:23:28,580 --> 01:23:30,590
总之你从大楼里
Somehow, you removed

1388
01:23:30,720 --> 01:23:33,380
移除了死危病毒恶意软件
the Severus malware from the building.

1389
01:23:33,520 --> 01:23:36,080
但你对自己的计划感到太兴奋
But you got excited about your plan,

1390
01:23:36,210 --> 01:23:39,910
喝多了向沃恩博士泄露了这事
you drank too much and told Dr. Vaughan about it.

1391
01:23:40,040 --> 01:23:41,490
你没想到的是
What you didn’t know

1392
01:23:41,630 --> 01:23:43,980
她的宗教信仰有多虔诚
is how profound her religious beliefs are.

1393
01:23:44,120 --> 01:23:45,500
你现在反咬我
You’re turning on me

1394
01:23:45,640 --> 01:23:47,220
是想掩盖自己的叛国行为
to cover up your own treasonous actions.

1395
01:23:47,360 --> 01:23:49,300
那种信仰不允许她
The kind of beliefs that would not permit her

1396
01:23:49,430 --> 01:23:51,990
坐视数万人因核泄漏丧生
to allow the deaths of tens of thousands in a meltdown.

1397
01:23:52,130 --> 01:23:53,510
都是妄想
This is a fantasy.

1398
01:23:53,640 --> 01:23:56,060
全是他妈的妄想
This is all one of his fucking fantasies.

1399
01:23:56,200 --> 01:23:58,130
所以最初我也很困惑
It’s why I had a hard time at first.

1400
01:23:58,270 --> 01:24:01,030
这不是一个计划 而是两个
It wasn’t one plan, you see, it was two.

1401
01:24:01,170 --> 01:24:03,070
独立却又环环相扣
Separate but interlocking.

1402
01:24:03,210 --> 01:24:06,590
既相互配合又彼此对抗
Working for and against each other.

1403
01:24:06,730 --> 01:24:10,390
你操纵我 让帕夫留克逃脱
You manipulated me so Pavlichuk could escape.

1404
01:24:10,520 --> 01:24:12,770
你和弗雷迪对凯瑟琳如法炮制
And you and Freddie did the same with Kathryn

1405
01:24:12,900 --> 01:24:16,560
这样就让她灭口他来保全我
so she would have him killed to bail me out.

1406
01:24:16,700 --> 01:24:19,500
因果循环
Causa et effectus.

1407
01:24:19,640 --> 01:24:21,670
对吗
Isn’t that right?

1408
01:24:21,810 --> 01:24:23,950
你们俩让这事变得太容易了
You two make it almost easy.

1409
01:24:24,090 --> 01:24:26,640
你们唯一在乎的只有彼此
The only thing you give a shit about is each other.

1410
01:24:26,780 --> 01:24:28,090
郑重声明 我早就知道
For the record, I knew.

1411
01:24:28,230 --> 01:24:30,780
但我还是做了 因为必须这么做
I did it anyway because it needed doing.

1412
01:24:30,920 --> 01:24:33,550
你还把我引到苏黎世
And you had me lured to Zurich.

1413
01:24:34,580 --> 01:24:37,450
我以为是要买回死危病毒
I thought I was buying back Severus,

1414
01:24:37,580 --> 01:24:40,040
结果你让我看起来像是在卖出
but you made it look like I was selling.

1415
01:24:40,170 --> 01:24:42,760
你在缅甸开的那个账户 是你自己操作的
You opened the account in Myanmar yourself,

1416
01:24:42,900 --> 01:24:44,520
对不对
didn’t you?

1417
01:24:45,590 --> 01:24:47,940
全是臆测
This is all conjecture.

1418
01:24:48,080 --> 01:24:49,460
结果发现
Turns out

1419
01:24:49,600 --> 01:24:52,810
缅甸方面很配合
Myanmar does cooperate.

1420
01:24:52,940 --> 01:24:57,920
只要找对人就行
You just have to know who to ask.

1421
01:25:04,720 --> 01:25:06,920
拉兹曼还欠我人情
Razman still owes me.

1422
01:25:13,340 --> 01:25:15,830
死危病毒是个好计划
Severus was a good plan.

1423
01:25:17,040 --> 01:25:19,970
再来十次我还会做同样选择
I’d do it again, ten times out of ten.

1424
01:25:21,010 --> 01:25:22,320
这个构思很巧妙
It was a decent frame,

1425
01:25:22,460 --> 01:25:25,530
本来可以终结这场该死的战争
and it would have ended the fucking war!

1426
01:25:28,150 --> 01:25:32,540
这是正确 勇敢 高尚的
It was right, it was brave, and it was noble.

1427
01:25:32,670 --> 01:25:34,610
哪个是你杀米查姆的理由
Which one was the reason you killed Meacham?

1428
01:25:37,300 --> 01:25:41,030
因为正确 还是因为高尚
Because it was right or because it was noble?

1429
01:25:43,240 --> 01:25:45,140
因为必要
Because it was necessary.

1430
01:25:45,270 --> 01:25:46,860
我从没告诉过你这个游戏的名字
I never told you all the name of the game.

1431
01:25:47,000 --> 01:25:48,690
什么游戏 凯瑟琳
What’s the game, Kathryn?

1432
01:25:48,830 --> 01:25:50,000
看谁先拔枪
"See Who Picks Up the Gun."

1433
01:25:50,140 --> 01:25:51,760
妈的
For fuck’s sake.

1434
01:25:51,900 --> 01:25:53,520
来吧 乔治
Come on, George.

1435
01:25:53,660 --> 01:25:55,700
怎样 给我戴上手铐带走
What? You take me out in handcuffs,

1436
01:25:55,840 --> 01:25:57,840
你说你的 我说我的 然后呢
you say your bit, I say mine, then what?

1437
01:25:57,980 --> 01:26:00,360
你还是会完蛋
You still go down.

1438
01:26:00,500 --> 01:26:02,190
她或许没事 但你肯定完蛋
Maybe she doesn’t, but you will.

1439
01:26:03,770 --> 01:26:06,540
你没有任何实锤证据
You got nothing... nothing hard.

1440
01:26:06,670 --> 01:26:09,610
只有怀疑 传闻和枕边风
You got suspicions, hearsay and pillow talk.

1441
01:26:11,160 --> 01:26:13,720
还有你的认罪录音
And, you know, your recorded confession.

1442
01:26:17,200 --> 01:26:19,580
谈谈你的投降条件
Shall we discuss the terms of your surrender?

1443
01:26:19,720 --> 01:26:22,450
你在虚张声势
You’re bluffing.

1444
01:26:22,590 --> 01:26:24,730
你该在船上就杀了我 乔治
You should’ve killed me on the boat, George.

1445
01:26:37,910 --> 01:26:39,600
我不介意你们做的事
Now, I don’t mind what you two did.

1446
01:26:39,740 --> 01:26:41,290
你们救了人
You saved lives.

1447
01:26:41,430 --> 01:26:44,570
但别再插手我的婚姻
But don’t ever fuck with my marriage again.

1448
01:26:45,920 --> 01:26:47,580
好的
Okay.

1449
01:26:50,300 --> 01:26:52,690
弗雷迪 桌子
Freddie. Table.

1450
01:26:58,070 --> 01:27:00,450
亲爱的 我们需要地毯
Darling, we need the rug.

1451
01:27:47,600 --> 01:27:49,220
九楼
Ninth floor.

1452
01:27:49,360 --> 01:27:50,400
电梯门开
Doors opening.

1453
01:28:00,270 --> 01:28:02,310
电梯下行
Lift going down.

1454
01:28:02,440 --> 01:28:04,270
电梯门关
Doors closing.

1455
01:28:06,900 --> 01:28:09,350
斯托克斯的事真糟糕
Terrible about Stokes.

1456
01:28:09,490 --> 01:28:11,590
-太蹊跷了 -是啊
-So strange. -Mm.

1457
01:28:11,730 --> 01:28:13,320
就这么消失了
Disappearing like that.

1458
01:28:13,460 --> 01:28:14,970
这行当确实危险
It’s a very dangerous line of work.

1459
01:28:15,110 --> 01:28:16,910
确实如此
Mm, I’ll say.

1460
01:28:19,010 --> 01:28:20,910
鉴于你的成就
Given all you’ve accomplished,

1461
01:28:21,050 --> 01:28:25,300
或许该考虑退休了 亚瑟
maybe it’s time to consider stepping away, Arthur.

1462
01:28:26,990 --> 01:28:28,710
先迈出去
Feet first.

1463
01:28:28,850 --> 01:28:29,750
二楼
Second floor.

1464
01:28:29,890 --> 01:28:32,410
电梯门开
Doors opening.

1465
01:28:32,540 --> 01:28:34,720
随你便
Any way you like.

1466
01:28:36,510 --> 01:28:38,380
电梯下行
Lift going down.

1467
01:28:38,520 --> 01:28:40,340
他完全慌了
He’s completely rattled.

1468
01:28:40,480 --> 01:28:42,100
太棒了
Fantastic.

1469
01:28:42,240 --> 01:28:44,000
够他一个月睡不着觉了
He won’t be able to sleep for a whole month.

1470
01:28:44,140 --> 01:28:45,380
他没慌
He wasn’t rattled.

1471
01:28:45,520 --> 01:28:48,250
他把所有功劳都揽走了
He took credit for the whole thing.

1472
01:28:48,390 --> 01:28:52,530
中情局那帮人正围着他大献殷勤
The CIA is lap dancing all over him.

1473
01:28:52,670 --> 01:28:54,050
都是假象
It’s a fiction.

1474
01:28:54,190 --> 01:28:55,700
他演不了多久
He won’t be able to keep it up forever.

1475
01:28:55,840 --> 01:28:58,190
施蒂格利茨让我感到无聊
And Stieglitz bores me.

1476
01:29:00,780 --> 01:29:04,580
我们 聊聊你吧
Let’s... let’s talk about you.

1477
01:29:04,710 --> 01:29:08,230
为什么不直接问我电影票的事
Why didn’t you just ask me about the movie ticket?

1478
01:29:08,370 --> 01:29:11,030
看我会不会撒谎
Hmm? See if I was lying?

1479
01:29:11,170 --> 01:29:13,070
信任
Faith.

1480
01:29:13,200 --> 01:29:15,240
你从不犯这种低级错误
You’d never be that sloppy.

1481
01:29:15,380 --> 01:29:17,210
电影票 太可笑了
A movie stub. Please.

1482
01:29:17,350 --> 01:29:19,490
确实
Well, exactly.

1483
01:29:20,450 --> 01:29:22,350
简直侮辱智商
It’s almost insulting.

1484
01:29:26,600 --> 01:29:29,430
-我知道你不会骗我 -除非必要
-I knew you’d never lie to me. -Only if I had to.

1485
01:29:29,570 --> 01:29:31,530
当然
Obviously.

1486
01:29:33,190 --> 01:29:35,090
有件事
One thing.

1487
01:29:35,230 --> 01:29:37,400
斯托克斯存进瑞士银行账户的
The, uh, seven million pounds

1488
01:29:37,540 --> 01:29:40,960
七百万英镑还在吗
Stokes put into the Swiss bank account?

1489
01:29:41,090 --> 01:29:42,230
还在
Still there.

1490
01:29:42,370 --> 01:29:44,550
哦 是吗
Oh. Is it?

